; Monotone co-batch negate fixture (checkpoint (d), analysis sec 4.5 R9,
; F-A case 1). negate_1 shape: a MONOTONE negated view (seen has no @never,
; feed/unsee non-differential), so only the `-` crossover arm exists.
;
; The load-bearing batch co-changes BOTH the pred row (feed(1,10) -> copy)
; AND the negated key (unsee(1) -> seen) in a SINGLE epoch. Under F-A
; convention A the forward firing is gated ABSENT-in-InI (seen(1) absent at
; batch start -> the forward +1 fires into out) while the `-` crossover
; scans the pred at InNew (copy(1,10) present by then -> a -1 fold), so the
; instance nets to ZERO and both stale crossings are claim-gate-dropped:
; out(1,10) must NEVER appear. A later batch that adds feed(2,20) without a
; matching unsee(2) confirms the ordinary (non-co-batch) forward path still
; publishes out(2,20). Latency probe: a subsequent unsee(2) (seen GAINS a
; key that already has a live pred row) must retract out(2,20) via the `-`
; crossover -- this is the standalone crossover-delete site, decoupled from
; the co-batch netting.
#message feed(i32 A, i32 B).
#message unsee(i32 A).

#local copy(i32 A, i32 B).
#local seen(i32 A).

#query out(free i32 A, free i32 B) : copy(A, B), !seen(A).

copy(A, B) : feed(A, B).
seen(A) : unsee(A).
